LICENSE.note for regdatasets
============================

The R code, documentation, and package infrastructure in this package are
released under the MIT License (see LICENSE and LICENSE.md files).

The datasets bundled in this package originate from various sources, each
with their own terms of use. The package author has made good-faith efforts
to include only datasets that are legally redistributable. Below is a
summary of each dataset's provenance and redistribution basis.

If you believe any dataset has been included in error, please contact the
package maintainer at jlee296@ua.edu.

Dataset-Level Provenance
========================

alcohol1_pp
  Source: Singer, J. D., & Willett, J. B. (2003). Applied Longitudinal
         Data Analysis. Oxford University Press.
  Basis: Companion data freely distributed by authors via UCLA OARC
         and Harvard ALDA website.

berk_sub, berkeley
  Source: Bickel, P. J., Hammel, E. A., & O'Connell, J. W. (1975).
         Sex bias in graduate admissions. Science, 187(4175), 398-404.
  Basis: Canonical public dataset widely redistributed in statistics
         textbooks and R packages (including base R's UCBAdmissions).

civic_ed
  Source: Tolo, K. W. (1999). The Civic Education of American Youth.
         Lyndon B. Johnson School of Public Affairs, University of Texas.
  Basis: Academic research data. Contact author/institution for
         redistribution confirmation.

classdata_07
  Source: Class survey data collected by the package author in 2007.
  Basis: Author-owned data. Anonymized (N=44).

crime
  Source: Florida Department of Law Enforcement. County-level crime
         statistics.
  Basis: US state government public records.

disc, disc2
  Source: National Center for Education Statistics (1988). National
         Education Longitudinal Study of 1988 (NELS:88).
  Basis: NELS:88 public-use data files. Subsets of NELS:88 public-use
         data are redistributed in multiple CRAN packages (CMatching,
         copulaData, faraway).

faculty
  Source: University faculty compensation study (specific source to be
         determined).
  Basis: Academic teaching dataset. Original source under investigation.

gcse
  Source: Goldstein, H., Rasbash, J., Yang, M., et al. (1993). A
         multilevel analysis of school examination results. Oxford Review
         of Education, 19(4), 425-433.
  Basis: Academic research data widely used in multilevel modeling
         textbooks. Available from University of Bristol CMM.

grades
  Source: Essay grading data from a writing assessment study (specific
         source to be determined).
  Basis: Academic teaching dataset. Original source under investigation.

gss_1
  Source: Smith, T. W., et al. General Social Survey. NORC at the
         University of Chicago.
  Basis: GSS public-use data is freely available from NORC for research
         use. The gssr R package (MIT license) bundles the full GSS
         cumulative data file. This package is not associated with or
         endorsed by NORC or the GSS.

hsb_sub, hsbs1
  Source: National Center for Education Statistics. High School and
         Beyond (HS&B) survey. Also: Raudenbush, S. W., & Bryk, A. S.
         (2002). Hierarchical Linear Models (2nd ed.). Sage.
  Basis: HS&B public-use data files. Subsets widely available in
         multilevel modeling textbooks and software.

individuals
  Source: U.S. Bureau of Labor Statistics. Current Population Survey,
         March 2000.
  Basis: US federal government data (public domain).

instruction
  Source: Hill, H. C., Rowan, B., & Ball, D. L. (2005). Effects of
         teachers' mathematical knowledge for teaching on student
         achievement. American Educational Research Journal, 42(2),
         371-406.
  Basis: Published academic research data.

lambert
  Source: Lambert, N. M. (1988). Adolescent outcomes for hyperactive
         children. American Psychologist, 43(10), 786-799.
  Basis: Published academic research data. Individual-level
         redistribution rights to be confirmed with original author
         or institution.

nels_data
  Source: National Center for Education Statistics (1988). National
         Education Longitudinal Study of 1988 (NELS:88).
  Basis: NELS:88 public-use data files. Confirm all 299 variables
         are from public-use (not restricted-use) files.

penalty
  Source: Agresti, A. (2002). Categorical Data Analysis (2nd ed.).
         Wiley. Original data: Radelet, M. L. (1981). Racial
         characteristics and the imposition of the death penalty.
         American Sociological Review, 46(6), 918-927.
  Basis: Widely redistributed in statistics textbooks.

pisa2000
  Source: OECD (2002). PISA 2000 Technical Report. Paris: OECD
         Publishing.
  Basis: OECD PISA public-use files. Multiple CRAN packages
         (learningtower, pisa) redistribute PISA data. The OECD
         Product License permits redistribution with proper
         attribution. This package is not associated with or
         endorsed by the OECD.

reading
  Source: Schmitt, M. C. (1987). The effects of an elaborated directed
         reading activity on the metacomprehension skills of third
         graders. Doctoral dissertation, Purdue University.
         Also in: Raudenbush & Bryk (2002).
  Basis: Published academic research data.

satisfaction
  Source: Simulated survey data for pedagogical purposes.
  Basis: Author-generated. No redistribution restrictions.

titanic
  Source: British Board of Trade (1990). Report on the Loss of the
         "Titanic" (S.S.). Historical public records.
  Basis: Historical public domain data. Widely redistributed.

womenlf
  Source: Fox, J. (2003). Applied Regression Analysis and Generalized
         Linear Models. Sage. Original data from the 1977 Canadian
         Social Change in Canada Project, York Institute for Social
         Research.
  Basis: Also available as carData::Womenlf on CRAN (GPL >= 2).
         A version of this dataset also appears in the carData package.
